 In order to deal with the political challenges of the climate change era—including the enactment of global justice, the future of democracy, and unpredictable surges in population movement—we must embrace the possibilities of human sovereignty while remaining mindful of its dangers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aDemocracyxPhilosophy. 0aPhilosophy, Frenchy20th century. 0aPolitical violence. 0aSovereignty. 4aArea Studies : French Studies. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 4aSociology : Violence. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848166140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438481661423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438481661/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles